    "comment": "Rationale: Immunoblotting of rat brain subcellular fractions indicates the presence of RhoB in synaptosomes.\n11/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper detects RhoB in the crude synaptic vesicle fraction (Sy) and the membrane-bound compartment fraction (Sy Mb) of the rat brain using a polyclonal antibody against RhoB. The quality of the images used in the additional literature field (PMID: 20203211) isn't optimal; and the juxtaposition with synaptophysin & colocalisation with PSD95 isn't robust to qualify the annotation to the SynGO term 'postsynapse'.\nBased on this, the generic term \"synapse\" was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods \"Isolation and Fractionation of Synaptic Vesicles from Rat Brain - Synaptic vesicles were prepared from rat brains according to Huttner et\nal.\"",
